    <title>Working with Processes</title>
    <para>The <guilabel>Processes</guilabel> view shows the configured process units (processes).
        The list of process units does not only comprise the process units configured by you but
        also two default process units: <guilabel>$SYSTEM</guilabel> and
            <guilabel>DEFAULT</guilabel>.</para>
    <para><indexterm>
            <primary>process unit</primary>
            <see>Process</see>
        </indexterm>
        <indexterm>
            <primary>configuration</primary>
            <secondary>process</secondary>
            <tertiary>$SYSTEM</tertiary>
        </indexterm><indexterm>
            <primary>$SYSTEM</primary>
            <secondary>process</secondary>
            <tertiary>configuration</tertiary>
        </indexterm><indexterm>
            <primary>configuration</primary>
            <secondary>process</secondary>
            <tertiary>DEFAULT</tertiary>
        </indexterm><indexterm>
            <primary>DEFAULT</primary>
            <secondary>process</secondary>
            <tertiary>configuration</tertiary>
        </indexterm></para>
    <note>
        <para>Please keep in mind that you must neither delete nor modify the default processes
                <guilabel>$SYSTEM</guilabel> and <guilabel>DEFAULT</guilabel> as they contain vital
            default and system-wide settings.</para>
    </note>
