    <sect1 xml:id="deploy_process">
        <title>Deploying the Process</title>
        <para>Use this action to deploy an existing process (file extension
                <filename>.dbe</filename>).</para>
        <note>
            <para>During deployment, you will be asked to select the desired DBE file from the
                directory tree. Therefore, before deployment, make sure that you know the location
                of the DBE file on your system.</para>
        </note>
        <para>Proceed as follows to deploy an existing process via the web interface.</para>
        <note>
            <para>Please keep in mind that you can also deploy processes from
                    <productname>&dbwp;</productname>. If you want to deploy processes via
                    <productname>&dbwp;</productname> as well as via
                    <productname>&dbpw;</productname>, make sure that the deployed processes do not
                overwrite each other.</para>
        </note>
        <procedure>
            <step>
                <para>Now switch to <guilabel>Processes</guilabel> view.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>In the navigation bar of the web interface, click <inlinemediaobject>
                        <alt>Create Button</alt>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata fileref="images/btn_add.png" align="left" format="PNG"
                                scalefit="1"/>
                        </imageobject>
                    </inlinemediaobject> (Deploy).</para>
                <result>
                    <para>The <guilabel>Deploy Process</guilabel> dialog opens. In the
                            <guilabel>Deploy Process</guilabel> dialog, you can override DBE file
                        settings.</para>
                </result>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>In the Deploy Process dialog, enter the systemnane in the field
                        <guilabel>System Name</guilabel>. By default, the value
                        <userinput>WIN64</userinput> is used. Alternatively, enter the value
                        <userinput>LIN64</userinput> for Linux systems.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>In the field <guilabel>DBE File Name</guilabel>, specify the name of the DBE
                    file you want to use. This setting is optional. Specifying the DBE file name is
                    useful if you are working with a ZIP archive with multiple DBE files or if the
                    ZIP archive does not contain a manifest file.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>Next to the text field <guilabel>Process Unit</guilabel>, click
                        <guibutton>Select File</guibutton> to select the file file from the
                    directory tree.</para>
                <result>
                    <para>The <guilabel>Open</guilabel> dialog opens.</para>
                </result>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>In the <guilabel>Open</guilabel> dialog, select the file from the directory
                    tree. This may be a single DBE file or a ZIP archive, for example.&nbsp;.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>In the <guilabel>Open</guilabel> dialog, click <guibutton>Open</guibutton> to
                    confirm your selection.</para>
                <result>
                    <para>The <guilabel>Open</guilabel> dialog closes and the file name of the
                        selected file is displayed in the <guilabel>Process Unit</guilabel>
                        field.</para>
                </result>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>In the <guilabel>Deploy Process</guilabel> dialog, click
                        <guibutton>OK</guibutton> to deploy the selected process..</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>The process is deployed, the <guilabel>Processes</guilabel> view is
                    automatically updated.</para>
                <result>
                    <para>If the deployment succeeded, the process is displayed in the
                            <guilabel>Processes</guilabel> view in the overview table.</para>
                </result>
            </step>
        </procedure>
    </sect1>
