    <sect1 xml:id="display_processes">
        <?dbhtml filename="SearchProcessView.html" ?>
        <title>Listing Processes</title>
        <para>You can display an overview of the existing (deployed) processes in the
                <guilabel>Processes</guilabel> view.</para>
        <mediaobject>
            <alt>Screenshot Processes view</alt>
            <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="images/scr_ProcessViewGen.png" width="15cm" format="PNG"/>
            </imageobject>
        </mediaobject>
        <para>The overview table displays the following information for each process by
            default:</para>
        <variablelist>
            <varlistentry>
                <term><guilabel>ID</guilabel></term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>The user-defined process name.</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <!--<varlistentry>
                <term><guilabel>Typ</guilabel></term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Aktuell wird nur der Wert <guilabel>processes</guilabel>
                        unterstützt.</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>-->
            <varlistentry>
                <term><guilabel>Tenant</guilabel></term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Mapping to a tenant. Indicates the tenant for which the process was
                        created. Unless specified otherwise, this field contains the default tenant
                            <guilabel>DEFAULT</guilabel>.</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term><guilabel>Version</guilabel></term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Optional. The process unit version for which the process was
                        deployed.</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term><guilabel>Comment</guilabel></term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Optional. Brief description or remarks about the process.</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
    </sect1>
    <sect1 xml:id="display_process_details">
        <title>Displaying Process Details</title>
        <para>You can display the details for a specific process in the details pane as follows: The
            details pane contains the same scope of information as the overview table.</para>
        <para>Click an entry in the overview table to display detailed information in the details
            pane.</para>
        <mediaobject>
            <alt>Details Pane</alt>
            <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="images/scr_ProcessViewDetails.png" align="left" width="15cm"
                    format="PNG"/>
            </imageobject>
        </mediaobject>
    </sect1>
    <sect1 xml:id="edit_process">
        <title>Modifying a Process</title>
        <para>Use this action to change the configuration settings of an existing process.</para>
        <para>Proceed as follows to edit the settings of a process.</para>
        <procedure>
            <step>
                <para>Now switch to <guilabel>Processes</guilabel> view.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>Select a process from the overview table.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>In the navigation bar of the web interface, click <inlinemediaobject>
                        <alt>Icon Edit</alt>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata fileref="images/btn_edit.png" align="left" format="PNG"
                                scalefit="1"/>
                        </imageobject>
                    </inlinemediaobject> (Edit).</para>
                <result>
                    <para>The selected entry in the overview table changes to editing mode.</para>
                </result>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>In the <guilabel>Tenant</guilabel> field, indicate to which tenant the process
                    is to be mapped.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>In the <guilabel>Version</guilabel> field, enter the version of the process
                    unit.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>In the <guilabel>Comment</guilabel> field, enter the desired text as
                    required.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <stepalternatives>
                    <step>
                        <para>Click <inlinemediaobject>
                                <alt>Save button</alt>
                                <imageobject>
                                    <imagedata fileref="images/btn_save.png" align="left"
                                        format="PNG" scalefit="1"/>
                                </imageobject>
                            </inlinemediaobject> (Save) to save the changes in the process
                            configuration and exit the editing mode for the selected entry.</para>
                        <result>
                            <para>The editing mode is terminated and the changes are displayed in
                                the overview table and in the detail pane of the selected
                                entry.</para>
                        </result>
                    </step>
                    <step>
                        <para>Click <inlinemediaobject>
                                <alt>Cancel button</alt>
                                <imageobject>
                                    <imagedata fileref="images/btn_cancel.png" align="left"
                                        format="PNG" scalefit="1"/>
                                </imageobject>
                            </inlinemediaobject> (Cancel) to cancel the changes and exit the editing
                            mode without saving the changes.</para>
                    </step>
                </stepalternatives>
            </step>
        </procedure>
    </sect1>
    <sect1 xml:id="multi_edit_processes">
        <title>Modifying Multiple Processes</title>
        <para>You can edit selected values for multiple processes in one step.</para>
        <note>
            <para>Please keep in mind that with this function, you define the same values for all
                selected processes.</para>
        </note>
        <para>Proceed as follows to edit the settings of the selected processes.</para>
        <procedure>
            <step>
                <para>Now switch to <guilabel>Processes</guilabel> view.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>Select at least two processes from the overview table.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>In the navigation bar of the web interface, click <inlinemediaobject>
                        <alt>Icon Edit</alt>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata fileref="images/btn_edit.png" align="left" format="PNG"
                                scalefit="1"/>
                        </imageobject>
                    </inlinemediaobject> (Edit).</para>
                <result>
                    <para>The <guilabel>Edit</guilabel> dialog opens.</para>
                </result>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>Tick the checkbox in front of each value you want to change for all selected
                    processes.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>In the <guilabel>Tenant</guilabel> field, specify the tenant to which the
                    selected processes are to be assigned.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>In the <guilabel>Version</guilabel> field, specify the version number for all
                    selected processes.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>In the <guilabel>Comment</guilabel> field, enter the desired text as
                    required.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <stepalternatives>
                    <step>
                        <para>Click <guibutton>OK</guibutton> to save the changed settings for all
                            selected processes and close the dialog.</para>
                        <result>
                            <para>The changed settings for the selected processes are displayed in
                                the overview table and in the details pane.</para>
                        </result>
                    </step>
                    <step>
                        <para>Click <guibutton>Cancel</guibutton> to close the dialog without
                            changing the settings.</para>
                    </step>
                </stepalternatives>
            </step>
        </procedure>
    </sect1>
    <sect1 xml:id="shareResource_process">
        <title>Sharing Process Permissions</title>
        <para>With the factory default settings of <productname>&dbpi;</productname>, users who have
            been assigned the <code>docpilot_admin</code> role have permissions for managing
            processes. Therefore, you (as a user assigned the <code>docpilot_admin</code> role) can
            share permissions for a selected process with other roles.</para>
        <para>Proceed as follows to share the permissions for a selected process with other
            roles.</para>
        <procedure>
            <step>
                <para>Now switch to <guilabel>Processes</guilabel> view.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>Select a process from the overview table.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>In the navigation bar of the view, click <inlinemediaobject>
                        <alt>Button Share resource</alt>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata fileref="images/btn_shareResource.png" align="left"
                                format="PNG" scalefit="1"/>
                        </imageobject>
                    </inlinemediaobject> (Share resource).</para>
                <result>
                    <para>The <guilabel>Share resource</guilabel> dialog opens.</para>
                    <mediaobject>
                        <alt>Share resource dialog</alt>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata fileref="images/dia_shareResource.png" align="left"
                                format="PNG" width="12cm"/>
                        </imageobject>
                    </mediaobject>
                </result>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>In the <guilabel>Share resource</guilabel> dialog, select the roles to which
                    you want to assign permissions for the selected process.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <stepalternatives>
                    <step>
                        <para>Click <guibutton>OK</guibutton> to confirm the changed permissions and
                            close the <guilabel>Share resource</guilabel> dialog.</para>
                    </step>
                    <step>
                        <para>Click <guibutton>Cancel</guibutton> to close the <guilabel>Share
                                resource</guilabel> dialog without changing the settings.</para>
                    </step>
                </stepalternatives>
            </step>
        </procedure>
    </sect1>
